&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fanatics Collectibles is seeking a&amp;nbsp;Commercial Operations Analyst, plays a critical role in enabling smooth and scalable commercial operations across retail, hobby, and data-driven sales channels in EMEA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role owns the execution of end-to-end order workflows, product and pricing governance, and system/data integrity across key platforms (D365, FC Pro, TM1). Acting as a central point of coordination between Sales, Finance, Logistics, and external partners, the role ensures operational accuracy, timely execution, and alignment across all commercial activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position requires a highly organised, detail-oriented individual who can manage multiple workflows simultaneously in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment, while maintaining strong data accuracy and stakeholder communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Order Creation &amp;amp; Revenue Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, validate, and process sales orders across retail, hobby, and international channels (D365 / FC Pro)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage complex order types including intercompany flows, manual orders, and pre-payment invoicing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own order accuracy, including pricing, allocation splits, and customer terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Issue order confirmations, dispatch documentation, and outbound communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor order lifecycle and proactively flag risks (e.g. payment issues, delays, discrepancies)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
